fields.description:
At present Fisheye/Crucible official documentation lacks information about some features that could cause security issues, such as:

- No mention that the access logs are disable by default;
- No information about anonymous access being enabled by default;
- No information that repositories allow anonymous access by default;

Even in documentation these default settings is not stated clearly:
- No information about insecure default permissions on the key pages of the documentation: fisheye configuration, repo configuration.
- Security best practice page does not have any information about default insecure settings (default enabled anonymous access)

It would be nice to be able to add a have some kind of query parameter to limit the results returned by the */rest-service-fecru/admin/*repositories endpoint based on the (url + path) of the repository. For example:
{code:java}
/rest-service-fecru/admin/repositories?url="http://example.com/svn/project1"
{code}
could only return the repositories whose (url + path) includes "http://example.com/svn/project1".

h3. Issue Summary

The link for Jetty documentation points to Codehaus website but they no longer exist and therefore, the link is a dead link.

Source - https://confluence.atlassian.com/fisheye/enabling-access-logging-in-fisheye-960155663.html

Bad Link:
{code:borderStyle=solid}
http://docs.codehaus.org/display/JETTY/Logging+Requests 
{code}

h3. Workaround

For further Jetty configuration, use the following:
{code:borderStyle=solid}
https://www.eclipse.org/jetty/documentation/current/configuring-jetty-request-logs.html{code}
